title: A Delightful Experience
text: Housed in a beautiful building, this market has every type of meat product, many types of cheese and dozens and dozens of eggs. It was delightful to talk to the vendors and learn about the local foods. The peppers stuffed with cheese or a cabbage mixture fascinated me. One vendor even offered me a sample of the cheese.

title: Nice For A Stroll
text: Curciluk Veliki is one of the many streets in the Bascarsija. There are a wide variety of shops and restaurants along the street. I really enjoyed taking a stroll on it.

title: Pretty Square
text: This is a pretty square along the pedestrian walkway with the Sarajevo Cathedral dominating it. There is a Sarajevo Rose in front of the cathedral.

title: Favorite Street
text: This was my favorite street in Bascarsija. One can visit the shops and find coppersmiths working on their copper products. They were very friendly and proud to show others their products.

title: Interesting to See
text: This is an interesting looking sculpture in a park next to the pedestrian walkway. During the Christmas season, it is next to an ice rink and an ice house.

title: Lovely Concept
text: This is such a lovely concept in a city that really suffered during the 1990s war. It is where the Bascarsija and the newer part of Sarajevo meet along the pedestrian walkway.

title: Nice Museum
text: It's always nice when old cities keep part of their history instead of tearing everything down and building over the ruins. It is very close to the Bascarsija and pedestrian walkway.

title: Impressive!
text: This impressive church is right off the pedestrian walkway across from a park. There are many pretty details in its architecture, so it's worth the short detour in order to view it.

title: Wide Variety of Things to Eat
text: When visiting a new city, I always enjoy going to the local market to help understand how the locals eat. This market is filled with a wide variety of items and friendly vendors. There is also a Sarajevo Rose at the back of the market.

title: Eye-Catching
text: This eye-catching cathedral is in a nice square along the pedestrian walkway. As one looks at the front of the church, there are reminders of the war on the bottom lefthand side of the building. There is also a Sarajevo Rose in front of the cathedral.

title: Lovely Walkway
text: This is a lovely pedestrian walkway that connects the Bascarsija with the other parts of Sarajevo. There is a wide selection of restaurants along the way. During the Christmas season, it goes right by an ice skating rink.

title: Plenty of Birds
text: This fountain is in a square in the Old Town and is close to the copper street. There were more birds than people and the birds aren't shy. Just don't look up with your mouth open.

title: Pretty Bridge
text: This is such a pretty bridge that will always be associated with the assassination of Arch Duke Ferdinand, which was the spark that started World War I. There is a plaque on the building on the old town side about the assassination.

title: Fascinating
text: It is always fascinating to to learn about different religions and visit their places of worship. This mosque is located in the middle of the Bascarsija. It has an interesting history.

title: Man's Inhumanity to Man
text: This small museum does an excellent job of showing man's inhumanity to man during the war in the 1990s. The audio guide is necessary in order to understand the poignant photographs displayed. Be sure to budget enough time to sit through the entire series of videos being shown. The stories of the wives and mothers are heartbreaking.

title: What's Not to Like Here?
text: What's not to like here? There are a variety of restaurants and the shopping is endless. It is very safe and clean and one just has to keep an eye for pickpockets, which are very common in Europe. Be sure to go down the street with all of the copper shops. The vendors are very friendly and may even demonstrate how they make some of the copper items. It was interesting to learn how this craft has been passed down through the generations. There are plenty of coffee sets available for sale.

title: The Resilience of the Residents of Sarajevo
text: The tunnel is a great example of the resilience the residents of Sarajevo displayed during that terrible four year seize. They were clever enough to build it perpendicular to the airport runway so that it could not be bombed. There is a very short segment of the tunnel that one can walk through and there is a room with a video. It is well worth visiting even though it can become crowded with tourists.

title: Great Location and Nice Hotel
text: This hotel is in the perfect location for exploring Sarajevo on foot. Just step out the front door and one is immediately in Bascarsija, Sarajevo's old town. Shopping and numerous restaurants are at one's fingertips. The hotel rooms were nice, quiet and clean. All of the hotel's employees were friendly and provided great service. The breakfast is good and one can even order a delicious omelet.

title: Can Be Crowded
text: The first time we stopped by, it was filled with tour groups. We walked around for awhile and came back and got a table. The service was friendly and prompt with the food being good and reasonabley priced.

title: Delicious
text: You won't go away hungry when you eat dinner here. From appetizer to dessert, everything was delicious and filling. The service was great, friendly and funny.

title: The Wide World of Baklava
text: I didn't realize how many varieties baklavas there are in this world. I got to taste several different ones and they all were delicious. The coffee drinkers said that the coffee was good and there was tea available for non coffee drinkers.

title: Delicious Food
text: The cevapi was delicious and was a generous portion. It was served with pita bread, onions, kajmak, and ajar. The apple dessert was also delicious. The service was great.

title: Pretty Location With Delicious Food
text: The restaurant is in a pretty location surrounded by vineyards. We were there for lunch and the food was delicious and the service was great. We enjoyed some great wine.

title: Striking Building
text: The Town Hall is a striking building at one end of the square. As one wanders through Varazdin, it is a good building to use as a landmark.

title: Make Major Reforms
text: This bishop made major reforms to religion in Croatia by using their national language during church services. There are three of these statues in Croatia.

title: Pretty Square
text: During the Christmas season, this pretty square is lined with booths selling drinks, food and various items. It was a lovely change from the crowded markets in Zagreb.

title: Pretty Castle
text: This is such a different and pretty looking castle. The museum inside has many interesting displays and rooms with period furniture. It really explains what life was like in earlier days.

title: Beautiful During the Christmas Season
text: This square is pretty all year around, but it is especially pretty during the Christmas season. It is lined with booths selling food and drinks and the lights are beautiful.

title: A Landmark
text: The Bell Tower really stands out in Old Town Zadar. It almost looks like it is leaning or is it an optical illusion? The chiming of the bells is quite impressive.

title: Delightful Park
text: This is a delightful, small park on the edge of Old Town. It is very peaceful compared to other parts of Old town Zadar. It is filled with beautiful trees and other plants. Many benches are spread throughout the park.

title: Middle of Old Town Zadar
text: This square is in the middle of Old Town Zadar and a short walking distance from anywhere in Old Town. People seem to gather here, so its a great spot to people watch. There was a pretty Christmas tree there during the Christmas season.

title: Pretty Building
text: This is a pretty building towering over a pretty square in the middle of Old Town Zadar. People seem to gather in this square because there are several restaurants there.

title: Splendid Promenade
text: This splendid promenade is a relaxing way to walk along the shoreline and to get to the Sea Organ and The Greeting to the Sun. It is lined by trees on the side by the city. There are plenty of places to sit and enjoy the scenery.

title: Quiet, Pretty, Little Park
text: This was a lovely discovery on our second trip to Zadar. It is a quiet, pretty, little park next to a busy square. It offers a pretty view of the Land City Gates as well as other parts of Zadar. There are plenty of benches so one can sit and enjoy nature.

title: Interesting to See
text: Right in the middle of Zadar, are some of the Roman remains of the forum. They are just parts of various former structures, but they are still interesting to see.

title: Unique Looking
text: This church looks very unique due to its uncommon shape. It's not as fancy as other churches but it is still impressive due to its age.

title: Beautiful Cathedral
text: It is a beautiful cathedral and it's within easy walking distance from anywhere in the old town. We were there on Christmas Day and could hear the congregation singing Christmas hymns. It was an unforgettable experience.

title: Off The Beaten Path
text: The gates are off the beaten path and next to a quiet, pretty harbor. The decorations on the gate are quite interesting. Looking down on the gates and harbor is a pretty view.

title: Perfect Location
text: The last time I was here, it was closed for repairs. I was delighted to see that it was back in operation. It is now surrounded by fencing because some people simply think it's fun to vandalize other's property. Be sure to stay after the sunset to enjoy the waves of various colors. It is fun to listen to children's squeals of delight as they watch it.
place: Greeting to the Sun - Il Saluto al Sole

title: Clever Idea
text: This is a clever idea in a beautiful setting. Depending on the waves, the organ can be very quiet or quite loud. It's a beautiful place to sit and watch the sunset over the water.

title: Delightful and Interesting
text: This is a delightful and interesting place. Our guide, Anna explained what farm life was like over 100 years ago. She infused humor in her excellent presentation. The farmhouse really illustrated that era.

title: Weather Happens
text: There are some things that can't be controlled and one of them is the weather. After days of rain, the area around the waterfalls was filled with water. The falls were massive and illustrated the power of water.

title: Plenty of Water
text: Due to plenty of rainfall, the falls were massive and many places were flooded so we were limited on where we could go.In spite of the flooding, it was very impressive. Now, I want to come back to see what it looks like under normal conditions.

title: Pretty Church
text: The Church of St. Gregory is a small, pretty church with a lovely rose window. Be sure to visit this church.

title: Unique Looking
text: This is an unique looking church with the clock and multiple bells. The bells look similar to what is seen in Greece. It is very close to St. James.

title: Impressive!
text: This monument is very impressive in the center of Sibenik. It looks out toward the harbor and during the Christmas season, it's right next to the Christmas Market.
place: Monument to Croatian King Petru Krešimiru IV

title: Interesting Building
text: This is an interesting building with an interesting history in a pretty location. It is in sharp contrast to the buildings above it.

title: Beautiful Cathedral
text: This is such an amazing and beautiful cathedral. The rose window is gorgeous and be sure to visit the stunning baptistery.
place: The Cathedral of St James in Sibenik

title: Beautiful Buildings
text: This is such a beautiful building in a pretty location. The arches make it very pleasing to the eyes.

title: Religious Items
text: This small museum is filled with many religious items. In order to enter, one must climb a flight of stairs.

title: Gorgeous Jewelry!
text: Such a delightful little shop that is filled to the brim with gorgeous coral jewelry. Everything is amazing and it was hard to narrow down my purchase. The sales clerk was very professional, helpful and patient with each customer.

title: Unique Tower
text: This tower stands out in the harbor due to its unique lack of height. It adds to the interesting variety of towers in Korcula.

title: Nice Museum
text: It's a nice, little museum that shows what life was like in earlier Croatia. There are a wide variety of interesting displays.

title: Interesting to See
text: The Korcula Town Walls help to delineate the older part of the town. Even though one can't walk on the walls, it's always interesting to discover the unique characteristics of each city's walls.

title: Charming Square
text: This charming square greets you right after going through the main gate. Once you enter, it is hard to decide which direction to go exploring. Don't worry, every direction is a delight.

title: Pretty Building
text: The clock tower is a very pretty building. It is on the main square and can be a great place to people watch.

title: Beautiful
text: For being such a small church, The Church of St. Clare is filled with so many beautiful things. It is a feast for the eyes.
place: Monastery and Church of St. Clare

title: Delicious Food and Great Entertainment
text: Set in an interesting building, this place offers delicious food and wine with great service. The dancers were fun to watch and the musicians were very talented. It was a lovely experience.

title: Very Educational
text: I never would have thought that Croatia is a place where they grow silk worms! This is a lovely shop with pretty items, some make with silk. We got to see how they turn silk worm cocoons into silk thread. Learning about the history and meaning of the different types of decorative silk bibs was quite fascinating. Luckily, people had the foresight to save and collect these historic, beautiful bibs.

title: Interesting Museum
text: This museum offers the naval history of Dubrovnik. Even though it is a small museum, it has interesting and informative displays with descriptions in English.
